7. Proses Pengujian Platform
7.1 Strategi Pengujian Komprehensif
7.1.1 Testing Pyramid
    /\
   /  \  E2E Tests (10%)
  /____\
 /      \ Integration Tests (20%)
/________\
Unit Tests (70%)
Unit Tests (70%):
•Test individual functions dan components
•Fast execution (< 1 second per test)
•Run on every code commit
•Examples: math calculations, form validations
Integration Tests (20%):
•Test interaction between modules
•Database operations
•API endpoint testing
•External service integrations
End-to-End Tests (10%):
•Critical user journeys
•Cross-browser compatibility
•Mobile app functionality
•Performance under load
7.2 Testing Environment Setup
7.2.1 Environment Configuration
# docker-compose.test.yml
version: '3.8'
services:
  app-test:
    build: .
    environment:
      - NODE_ENV=test
      - DATABASE_URL=postgresql://test:test@db-test:5432/geosync_test
    depends_on:
      - db-test
      - redis-test
  
  db-test:
    image: postgres:14
    environment:
      - POSTGRES_DB=geosync_test
      - POSTGRES_USER=test
      - POSTGRES_PASSWORD=test
  
  redis-test:
    image: redis:7-alpine
7.2.2 Test Data Management
Test Data Strategy:
•FactoryBot untuk data generation
•Database transactions isolation
•Seed data untuk consistent testing
•Cleanup procedures after each test
7.3 User Acceptance Test (UAT)
7.3.1 UAT Planning
Participants:
•5 power users dari client
•2 domain experts
•1 project manager
•1 quality assurance representative
Test Scenarios:
Scenario	Description	Expected Result
New Project Creation	Create complete project with team	Project saved with all metadata
Borehole Data Entry	Enter SPT data via mobile app	Data synced to server correctly
Report Generation	Generate geotechnical report	PDF produced with correct data
Offline Sync	Collect data offline, sync when online	All data preserved and synced
7.3.2 UAT Execution Process
1.Preparation Phase (1 week):
–Environment setup
–Test data preparation
–User training session
2.Execution Phase (2 weeks):
–Guided testing sessions
–Independent testing periods
–Bug documentation
3.Evaluation Phase (1 week):
–Results analysis
–Bug prioritization
–Acceptance criteria review
7.4 Parallel Run Strategy
7.4.1 Phased Approach
Phase 1: Shadow Mode (2 weeks)
•New system runs alongside existing
•No real operations on new system
•Data validation between systems
•Performance comparison
Phase 2: Partial Migration (4 weeks)
•25% operations migrated to new system
•Critical operations remain on legacy
•User feedback collection
•Issue resolution
Phase 3: Full Migration (2 weeks)
•100% operations on new system
•Legacy system on standby
•Intensive monitoring
•Rollback plan ready
7.4.2 Success Criteria
Functional Criteria:
•100% core features working
•< 1% data discrepancy
•Response time < 2 seconds
•99.9% uptime
User Acceptance Criteria:
•90%+ user satisfaction score
•< 5 critical issues reported
•Training completion rate 100%
•Support ticket resolution < 24 hours

